## Experience


### Director, Technology

`2022 May -` *current*, **[Creative Commons (CC)][cc]**, Full-Time Remote

- Management
  - Manage technology team (planning, sprints, 1:1s, career development)
  - Provide technical guidance to organizational leadership
  - Cultivate a culture of psychological safety, curiosity, collaboration, and
    care that pursues positive change
  - Work to minimize risks and ensure business continuity (change management,
    backup policies, security policies)
- Python Development
  - Develop applications and integrations (Django, MariaDB, PostgreSQL, Python,
    SQLite)
  - Champion Python and guide its use at CC (best practices, packaging,
    style guide)
  - Maintain a working knowledge of other programming languages in use at CC
    (Bash, JavaScript, PHP)
  - Improve our code quality through automation, code reviews, and unit tests
  - Deploy and manage infrastructure as code (IaC) (ex. Ansible, AWS, Docker,
    GitHub Actions, Heroku, Linux, SaltStack)
- Project Management and Collaboration
  - Manage key projects (CC Legal DB, CC Legal Tools, Quantifying the
    Commons)
  - Participate in oncall rotation (UptimeRobot, PagerDuty)
  - Provide support (GitHub Pull Request reviews) and coverage for team
    members
  - Mentor work program contributors (Google Summer of Code, Outreachy, various
    university programs)
  - Champion working transparently in the open and contributing to a welcoming
    and supportive community
  - Champion free/libre and open source software (FOSS)

